- 'Ball tree' refers to a data structure and algorithm for organizing and searching large sets of points in multi-dimensional space;
- 'Active' models are those currently in use or deployed;
- Mean fit time, mean test NMSE (Normalized Mean Squared Error), and mean test R2 are metrics to evaluate model performance;
- Access types (e.g., view, edit) indicate the level of interaction a user had with a model.

NMSE (Normalized Mean Squared Error) and R2 (Coefficient of Determination) are metrics used to evaluate the performance of models; 
A lower NMSE value indicates better performance, while a higher R2 value indicates better performance; 
The query is designed to determine the better metric for each model by comparing the average NMSE and R2 values.

sql:
SELECT hyperparameter_id, neighbors
FROM hyperparameters
ORDER BY neighbors DESC;

SELECT model_id 
FROM models 
ORDER BY model_id ASC;
